MediaPipe Pose Estimation Docker Container for Jetson

To build and run:

  # Allow X11 display access from container
  xhost +local:docker

  # Build the container
  docker compose build

  # Run with the default script (mediapipe_pose.py - USB camera)
  docker compose up

  # Or run a specific script
  docker compose run mediapipe-pose python3 mediapipe_pose_gstreamer.py   # CSI camera
  docker compose run mediapipe-pose python3 mediapipe_pose_data.py        # CSI + data extraction

Available scripts:
  - mediapipe_pose.py: Basic pose detection with USB camera (V4L2)
  - mediapipe_pose_gstreamer.py: Pose detection with CSI camera via GStreamer
  - mediapipe_pose_data.py: Pose detection with landmark data extraction

Key features:
  - NVIDIA runtime enabled for GPU acceleration
  - Camera devices mounted (/dev/video0 for USB, plus CSI camera nodes)
  - X11 socket shared for GUI display
  - Python files mounted as volumes for easy development (changes reflect
    without rebuild)
  - Privileged mode and host network for full hardware access

Base image: nvcr.io/nvidia/l4t-base:r36.2.0 (Ubuntu 22.04, JetPack 6.x)        
